      "name": "add-delivery-method-terms",                                    
      "prompt": "Please add 22 new terms to the EFO ontology file at          
  /home/runner/work/efo/efo/src/ontology/efo-edit.owl.\n\nThese terms relate  
  to nucleic acid delivery methods and nucleic acid integration states, all   
  under Transfection (EFO:0000726).\n\n**Current state:** The last EFO_092xxxx
  ID used is EFO_0920063. New terms should start from EFO_0920064.\n\n**All   
  terms to add (22 total):**\n\n---\n\n**1. EFO_0920064 - nucleic acid        
  delivery method**\n- Label: nucleic acid delivery method\n- Definition: A   
  transfection that describes the means by which nucleic acid molecules (DNA  
  or RNA) are physically or chemically introduced into target cells.\n-       
  Parent: EFO:0000726 (transfection)\n- organizational_class: true\n- PMIDs   
  for definition: 41593732, 41498563\n\n**2. EFO_0920065 - viral transduction 
  method**\n- Label: viral transduction method\n- Definition: A nucleic acid  
  delivery method that uses viral vectors to introduce nucleic acid cargo into
  target cells by exploiting viral mechanisms of cell entry and genome        
  delivery.\n- Parent: EFO_0920064 (nucleic acid delivery method)\n-          
  organizational_class: true\n- PMIDs for definition: 41494593,               
  41593732\n\n**3. EFO_0920066 - stable viral transduction method**\n- Label: 
  stable viral transduction method\n- Definition: A viral transduction method 
  in which the viral nucleic acid cargo stably integrates into the host cell  
  genome, enabling heritable and long-term transgene expression.\n- Parent:   
  EFO_0920065 (viral transduction method)\n- organizational_class: true\n-    
  PMIDs for definition: 41800026, 41593679\n\n**4. EFO_0920067 - lentivirus   
  transduction**\n- Label: lentivirus transduction\n- Definition: A stable    
  viral transduction method that uses lentiviral vectors, derived from        
  lentiviruses such as HIV-1, to deliver nucleic acid cargo into both dividing
  and non-dividing cells via stable integration into the host chromosomal DNA.
  \n- Parent: EFO_0920066 (stable viral transduction method)\n- Synonyms:     
  lentiviral transduction (hasExactSynonym)\n- PMIDs for definition: 41800026,
  41593679\n\n**5. EFO_0920068 - retrovirus transduction**\n- Label:          
  retrovirus transduction\n- Definition: A stable viral transduction method   
  that uses retroviral vectors, derived from oncoretroviruses such as         
  gammaretroviruses, to deliver nucleic acid cargo into dividing cells via    
  stable integration of the retroviral genome into the host chromosomal DNA.\n-
  Parent: EFO_0920066 (stable viral transduction method)\n- Synonyms:         
  retroviral transduction (hasExactSynonym)\n- PMIDs for definition: 41445185,
  41494593\n\n**6. EFO_0920069 - transient viral transduction method**\n-     
  Label: transient viral transduction method\n- Definition: A viral           
  transduction method in which the viral nucleic acid cargo enters target     
  cells but does not stably integrate into the host genome, resulting in      
  transient transgene expression that is lost upon cell division.\n- Parent:  
  EFO_0920065 (viral transduction method)\n- organizational_class: true\n-    
  PMIDs for definition: 41746105, 41624053\n\n**7. EFO_0920070 - adenovirus   
  transduction**\n- Label: adenovirus transduction\n- Definition: A transient 
  viral transduction method that uses adenoviral vectors to deliver nucleic   
  acid cargo into target cells, where the viral DNA persists as an episomal   
  element without integrating into the host genome.\n- Parent: EFO_0920069    
  (transient viral transduction method)\n- Synonyms: adenoviral transduction  
  (hasExactSynonym)\n- PMIDs for definition: 41746105, 41852322\n\n**8.       
  EFO_0920071 - adeno-associated virus transduction**\n- Label: adeno-        
  associated virus transduction\n- Definition: A transient viral transduction 
  method that uses adeno-associated virus (AAV) vectors to deliver nucleic    
  acid cargo into target cells, where the vector DNA predominantly persists as
  episomal concatemers with minimal integration into the host genome.\n-      
  Parent: EFO_0920069 (transient viral transduction method)\n- Synonyms: adeno-
  associated viral transduction (hasExactSynonym), AAV transduction           
  (hasRelatedSynonym)\n- PMIDs for definition: 41785320, 41736770\n\n**9.     
  EFO_0920072 - herpes virus transduction**\n- Label: herpes virus            
  transduction\n- Definition: A transient viral transduction method that uses 
  herpesviral vectors, derived from herpesviruses such as herpes simplex virus
  (HSV), to deliver nucleic acid cargo into target cells, particularly neurons,
  without permanent integration into the host genome.\n- Parent: EFO_0920069  
  (transient viral transduction method)\n- Synonyms: herpesviral transduction 
  (hasExactSynonym), HSV vector transduction (hasRelatedSynonym)\n- PMIDs for 
  definition: 41581759, 41705810\n\n**10. EFO_0920073 - non-viral transfection
  method**\n- Label: non-viral transfection method\n- Definition: A nucleic   
  acid delivery method that uses physical or chemical approaches other than   
  viral vectors to introduce nucleic acids into target cells.\n- Parent:      
  EFO_0920064 (nucleic acid delivery method)\n- organizational_class: true\n- 
  PMIDs for definition: 40733113, 41820622\n\n**11. EFO_0920074 -             
  electroporation**\n- Label: electroporation\n- Definition: A non-viral      
  transfection method in which brief, high-voltage electrical pulses are      
  applied to cells, transiently permeabilizing the plasma membrane to allow   
  uptake of nucleic acids into the cell.\n- Parent: EFO_0920073 (non-viral    
  transfection method)\n- PMIDs for definition: 40733113, 41600998\n\n**12.   
  EFO_0920075 - nucleofection**\n- Label: nucleofection\n- Definition: A non- 
  viral transfection method that combines cell-type-specific electrical       
  parameters and proprietary reagents to deliver nucleic acids directly into  
  the nucleus of cells, including difficult-to-transfect primary and non-     
  dividing cells.\n- Parent: EFO_0920073 (non-viral transfection method)\n-   
  PMIDs for definition: 39601181, 41181132\n\n**13. EFO_0920076 -             
  lipofection**\n- Label: lipofection\n- Definition: A non-viral transfection 
  method in which cationic lipid formulations spontaneously form complexes    
  with negatively charged nucleic acids and fuse with the cell membrane to    
  deliver the nucleic acid cargo into target cells.\n- Parent: EFO_0920073    
  (non-viral transfection method)\n- Synonyms: lipid-mediated transfection    
  (hasRelatedSynonym), liposome-mediated transfection (hasRelatedSynonym)\n-  
  PMIDs for definition: 40733113, 41047124\n\n**14. EFO_0920077 - nano-       
  particle mediated transfection**\n- Label: nano-particle mediated           
  transfection\n- Definition: A non-viral transfection method in which        
  nanoparticles, such as polymeric, inorganic, or lipid nanoparticles, are    
  used as carriers to encapsulate and deliver nucleic acid cargo into target  
  cells.\n- Parent: EFO_0920073 (non-viral transfection method)\n- Synonyms:  
  nanoparticle-mediated transfection (hasExactSynonym)\n- PMIDs for           
  definition: 41869399, 41820622\n\n**15. EFO_0920078 - microinjection**\n-   
  Label: microinjection\n- Definition: A non-viral transfection method in     
  which a fine glass capillary needle is used under microscopic guidance to   
  directly inject nucleic acids or other macromolecules into individual cells.
  \n- Parent: EFO_0920073 (non-viral transfection method)\n- PMIDs for        
  definition: 41514701, 33241661\n\n**16. EFO_0920079 - optical               
  transfection**\n- Label: optical transfection\n- Definition: A non-viral    
  transfection method in which a focused laser beam creates transient pores in
  the cell membrane, enabling the entry of nucleic acids into the cell without
  mechanical penetration.\n- Parent: EFO_0920073 (non-viral transfection      
  method)\n- Synonyms: optoporation (hasRelatedSynonym), photoporation        
  (hasRelatedSynonym), laser transfection (hasRelatedSynonym), optoinjection  
  (hasRelatedSynonym)\n- PMIDs for definition: 38321124, 38245895\n\n**17.    
  EFO_0920080 - sonoporation**\n- Label: sonoporation\n- Definition: A non-   
  viral transfection method that uses ultrasound waves, often combined with   
  microbubbles, to transiently permeabilize cell membranes and facilitate     
  cellular uptake of nucleic acids.\n- Parent: EFO_0920073 (non-viral         
  transfection method)\n- Synonyms: ultrasound-mediated transfection          
  (hasRelatedSynonym)\n- PMIDs for definition: 41075407, 41600998\n\n**18.    
  EFO_0920081 - nucleic acid integration state**\n- Label: nucleic acid       
  integration state\n- Definition: A property of a transfected nucleic acid   
  that describes the mode by which the delivered nucleic acid persists in the 
  host cell in relation to the host genome, including integration into        
  chromosomal DNA or episomal persistence.\n- Parent: EFO:0000726             
  (transfection)\n- organizational_class: true\n- PMIDs for definition:       
  41593679, 41820622\n\n**19. EFO_0920082 - random locus integration**\n-     
  Label: random locus integration\n- Definition: A nucleic acid integration   
  state in which the delivered nucleic acid inserts into the host genome at   
  non-specific, random chromosomal locations, as typically occurs with        
  retroviral and lentiviral vectors.\n- Parent: EFO_0920081 (nucleic acid     
  integration state)\n- Synonyms: random integration (hasExactSynonym)\n-     
  PMIDs for definition: 41593679, 41445185\n\n**20. EFO_0920083 - targeted    
  locus integration**\n- Label: targeted locus integration\n- Definition: A   
  nucleic acid integration state in which the delivered nucleic acid is       
  directed to integrate at a specific, pre-defined chromosomal locus using    
  site-specific recombination systems or precision genome editing tools.\n-   
  Parent: EFO_0920081 (nucleic acid integration state)\n- Synonyms: site-     
  specific integration (hasExactSynonym), targeted integration                
  (hasExactSynonym)\n- PMIDs for definition: 41820622, 41705810\n\n**21.      
  EFO_0920084 - native locus replacement**\n- Label: native locus             
  replacement\n- Definition: A nucleic acid integration state in which the    
  delivered nucleic acid sequence replaces an endogenous sequence at the      
  native genomic locus via homology-directed repair, preserving the natural   
  chromosomal context.\n- Parent: EFO_0920081 (nucleic acid integration       
  state)\n- Synonyms: knock-in (hasRelatedSynonym), homologous replacement    
  (hasRelatedSynonym)\n- PMIDs for definition: 41820622, 41705810\n\n**22.    
  EFO_0920085 - not-integrative transgene expression**\n- Label: not-         
  integrative transgene expression\n- Definition: A nucleic acid integration  
  state in which the delivered nucleic acid persists episomally in the host   
